:''For the condition where school is cancelled due to weather, see [[Snow day]].''

[[Image:Emmanuelle_chriqui_mark_webber_promo_still_snow_day.jpg|right|thumb|[[Mark Webber (actor)|Mark Webber]] and [[Emmanuelle Chriqui]] in Paramount's [[Snow Day]].]]'''''Snow Day''''' ([[2000]]) is an [[United States|American]] [[comedy]] [[film]] by [[Paramount Pictures]] and [[Nickelodeon Movies]].  The film focuses on a group of elementary students in [[Syracuse, New York]], (led by Natalie Brandston) who try to keep their school snowed-in and closed by stopping a [[snow plow]] driver from plowing the streets. Meanwhile, her older brother Hal tries to win the heart of high school sweetheart Claire Bonner.  Also, their dad (Tom Brandston) is a TV meteorologist who must face off against a rival meteorologist in order to have the right of continuing their weather career. It was filmed in [[Edmonton]] and [[Calgary]], [[Alberta]], [[Canada]]. It was originally planned to be a movie based on the [[television series]] ''[[The Adventures of Pete & Pete]]'', but Paramount was not interested in making a film based on the series. The single "[[Another Dumb Blonde]]" was released from the soundtrack.

